  "prompt": "What are the best small classes for freshmen at Southern Connecticut State?",
  "response": "Southern Connecticut State University offers various small classes for freshmen that can enhance the learning experience through personalized attention and interaction. While the specific course offerings can vary each semester, here are a few types of classes and subjects that often have smaller enrollment numbers and are popular among freshmen:\n\n1. **First-Year Seminar Courses**: These classes are specifically designed for freshmen and cover a range of topics while focusing on developing skills in critical thinking, writing, and research.\n\n2. **Introductory Courses in the Arts and Humanities**: Classes in subjects like art, music, and literature often have smaller class sizes, allowing for more discussions and deeper engagement.\n\n3. **Science and Lab Courses**: Some introductory science courses, especially those with accompanying lab components, may have smaller sections available.\n\n4. **Foreign Language Classes**: Introductory language courses tend to have smaller class sizes, providing an intimate setting for students to practice speaking and engage with the material.\n\n5. **Writing and Composition Courses**: These courses often have limited enrollment to facilitate individual feedback on writing assignments.\n\nTo find the best options, it\u2019s a good idea for freshmen to consult the academic catalog, speak with academic advisors, and consider their interests when selecting courses. Checking for details about class size and availability can also be helpful during course registration.",
